history.text: heelo
hi!
Hello
Have you seen the Social Network?
Yes I have! Brilliant film.
Did you feel it was a good representation of how facebook began?
are you planning on watching?
I have seen it several years ago and have a vague recollection of it.
I don't know to be fair. Some people say that the directors took some creative liberties in the biographical dimension of the film.
I agree and did not realize that Mark Zuckerberg was not involved in this project.
Do you generally watch movies with high ratings on Rotten Tomatoes from the public, or do you listen more to what the critics say?
I'm more keen on Metacritic. in any case it had stellar reviews in both
Have you read the book, The Accidental Billionaires: The Founding of Facebook, that The Social Network on which The Social Network was based?
No I haven't'. I can't say that this is a topic that interests me much.
I agree. So, is this not the normal genre of movies that interests you?
I'm more fond of action movies. But this picture also has some interesting scenes.
Do you agree with the rating of the movie?
96% on rotten tomatoes and 95/100 on metacritic seem a bit high
What would you give it?
I would rate it in the 80's range
I would agree with that. It was definitely a good portrayal of the story, but nothing exceptional.
there are however some good individual performances

what did you think of Jesse Eisenberg
 as Zuckerberg?
I thought he did a pretty decent job. That's why I thought Mark Zuckerberg must've been involved in the project in order to see things from his viewpoint.
You think he risks being typecasted? can only play "zuckerberg" types in the future?
Not at all. I just think it is his most widely know film. He's had other productions, but nothing as well-received as this one.
you think Zuckerberg's reputation is enhanced or belittled by the film?
I can't remember all of the details of this movie, but I think people learned the truth about how facebook really began, and I'm not sure it does much to enhance his reputation.
Do you know how we move to the next part of this survey, since we have completed the chat portion?
In one of the final scenes Zuck's lawyers advise him to make an agreement with Saverin because the jury wasn't sympathetic to him. You got the same feeling?
it's done
